59 In Rogers v The Queen [1994] HCA 42 ; (1994) 181 CLR 251 at 286, Mason CJ, after remarking that categories of abuse of process remain open, identified three categories within which abuse of process usually falls: (1) the court's procedures are invoked for an illegitimate purpose;
(2) the use of the court's procedures is unjustifiably oppressive to one of the parties; or
(3) the use of the court's procedures would bring the administration of justice into disrepute.
